-LXboZsceFoTkIYrwu0r.description:
This took, conservatively, at least forty hours to draw, as it is composed of thousands of tiny dots and hair-fine lines drawn with an extremely fine Micron pen. It depicts the Hopf fibration, a stereographic projection of the four-dimensional sphere into regular 3-space, as a bundle of pineapple-scaled Hopf bands.
The concepts behind the piece and the techniques I used to create it came together incredibly smoothly. I knew I wanted to create a piece featuring a pineapple, because it would allow me to work in hexagonal tessellations and organic material. The Hopf fibration stood out as a perfect application for pineapple scales because I wanted something that would have parallels to the bands seen in the fibration, and pineapples provided that.
-LXboZsceFoTkIYrwu0r.title: Hopf Fibration With Pineapple Scales

-LZ0PJ4LlrIwAWv5MgJa.description:
MURMURATIONS
Luke Farrell
Jake Shulman

This work is inspired by the murmurations formed by Startling birds -- a classically emergent system found in nature. Here we use a python implementation to create a stochastic generative algorithm that simulates these murmurations. Introducing velocity rules, collision avoidance, circularly evading prey, and other properties allow this emergent system to trace complex patterns over time. The paths traced represent the attraction of multiple pairs of birds in the flock as they move overtime. Each of the murmuration patterns represents an increasingly weighted prey attraction parameter and longer pursuit left to right and the colors are randomly sampled from images of tropical flocking birds.
-LZ0PJ4LlrIwAWv5MgJa.title: Murmuration

-LZ0y3TFR6BqJb4Rc4dm.description: This was a piece created for no other purpose than to be different. And yet in its differentness one can find resonance with the life of a college student. College is a stressful time, all-consuming, enough to make on cringe and cry. It feels as though we work through this mental jungle gym of anxiety, depression, pressure and more pressure again, for the little pieces of molten success, liquid gold: a good grade, a scholarship won, an opportunity taken full advantage of. But despite each drop of golden victory upon our skin, upon our minds, we still scrape and claw and strive for more.
-LZ0y3TFR6BqJb4Rc4dm.title: Sarah Melting

-LZ0zmUjuYHBv_cGh07p.description: At the center of the Oglesby family structure was Annie Oglesby. For years, I marveled at my inspirational grandmother who, despite her inability to hear, successfully raised four kids within the public housing communities of Dayton, Ohio. Her house was the connection which brought the family together, her cooking made in that way that only your grandmother could. It was her strictness, her love, and her dedication that made her house a home, for my father and for me. We just came up on the third anniversary of her passing in February, an annual event that seems to displace all of us. I painted this picture for my dad for Father's Day, in loving memory of my grandmother. As a tribute to her life and the home she created, my father usually has this painting set upon a shrine next to her photo, some roses, and her ashes. And in tribute to her legacy, he has allowed me to share it with those at Duke.
-LZ0zmUjuYHBv_cGh07p.fileName: Cameron Oglesby-In Loving Memory of Annie Oglesby.jpg
-LZ0zmUjuYHBv_cGh07p.title: In Loving Memory of Annie Oglesby

-LZ1-vVwXBldPh3dFyE9.description: This is just a picture of my little brother. In an attempt to pin down the human form, I asked him to dance to the music he was listening to as a I snapped a reference image. This was the first piece that I did that actually truly looked like the person I was drawing and from it, came a series of other human and figure drawings and paintings and an overall greater confidence in my artistic capabilities. Although we planned to frame it, it's been in and out of so many galleries that we've decided to keep it as is and continue to share my first "human" success with the world .
-LZ1-vVwXBldPh3dFyE9.title: Now Watch Me Whip

-LZM3w6TRXzlaEKEOZv-.description: Squirrelyn Monroe  is a spin off on Andy Warhol s famous Marylin Monroe screenprint. Warhol s original sought to convey the dehumanization of Hollywood stars like Monroe  whose face he printed over and over again so that an onlooker would become so desensitized to its appearance that the faces would seem to seize to represent an actual human being. The screenprint mimics the repeated images portrayed in the media that Americans are equally desensitized to. Similarly   Squirrelyn Monroe   in a more lighthearted approach  presents a desensitization of students to the countless squirrels on Duke s campus and perhaps the squirrels  desensitization to us.
-LZM3w6TRXzlaEKEOZv-.title: Squirrelyn Monroe

-LZvoM2i4ciMpYTc3xvF.description: As a first generation American citizen whose parents immigrated from India  I ve had too many identities but not enough of one. Most of the representation Indians receive in Western media is misrepresentation. Therefore  I found some comfort in hip hop and urban culture  which are built on representation and authenticity. They gave me a way to navigate my cultural surroundings and eventually became a significant part of my identity.   On my path to cultural reconciliation and healing  I ve found blending aspects of my various identities to be therapeutic. I wanted to explore the relationship between Hindu deities and our perception of them. In typical Hindu shrines  most of them are portrayed in a grandiose manner   draped in jewelry and vibrant Indian clothing in front of a colorful background. By adding pieces of streetwear to photos of these deities and removing some ornaments  I wanted them to represent my cultural existence. I also wanted to explore how replacing more ancient signs of wealth with contemporary signs of wealth would influence my perception of these deities.
-LZvoM2i4ciMpYTc3xvF.dimensions: Artwork is a digital image  so dimensions can vary based on print.
-LZvoM2i4ciMpYTc3xvF.title: Hip Hop and Hinduism
